  "text": "Magnetic Resonance Imaging (1.5T MRI scanner Signa GE, Milwaukee, USA) was performed in Ⅳ3 (proband) and Ⅳ20, and PET-CT imaging was carried out in Ⅳ1, Ⅳ3 and Ⅳ20. In MRI examination, the T1-weighted (T1W), T2-weighted (T2W) studies were available in our cases. 11 C-CFT uptake studies and PD-related covariance pattern (PDRP) based on [CITATION_1] F-fluorodeoxyglucose (FDG) positron emission tomography (PET) scans from Ⅳ1, Ⅳ3 and Ⅳ20 were performed in three-dimensional (3D) mode on a Siemens Biograph TruePoint PET•CT (Siemens healthcare, Munich, Bavaria, Germany), producing image slices over the whole brain with an intrinsic 3D resolution.",
